 whole lot fun. The Jewelbag makes it not so hard if you lost your Miner on the way back home, the Coins let you buy some abilitys wile youre digging and the Weapons work more as tools (at least that was my idea) you can use if you need them.\n\n\n\n\n[b]But i have to be honest.[/b]\nIt sure is a nice game and i played it for a long time as i got it and as the Dev build in all the new ideas and co but after a wile it got a bit \"boring\" and now i play it more \"ones in a wile\". Again, i really [b]love[/b] the idea and the game, mixing 2 great games from not only my childhood.\n\nThe problem i have (at least) is that this said \"main part\" (here i come back to it) has not really any kind of \"goal\".\nIts not like Lemmings where you actually have to save a number of Lemmings or Boulder Dash where you have to collect a number of gems and find the exit.\n\nIt sure mixes the gameplay very ([b]VERY[/b]) well but it misses the side of \"complied\" something:\nYou dig around with abilitys which you also have to buy again after using a said ability. You get money by either collecting a coin or bring back gems/jewels back to your home. If you bring said gems/jewels back to your home, you buy with the money you get from them said abilitys and go digging, returning into the circle ones again.\n\nIts not like it is a bad idea, the problem is just it misses something \"why\" youre going to dig in the first place.\nLet me explain that:\nIf i buy me a pickaxe [b]just[/b] to dig around and get a jewel, bring it back home, selling it [b]just[/b] for buying myself [b]another[/b] pickaxe.....i guess you see what i try to explain...\n\nIt misses a kind of \"goal\" to be honest. Something like you \"have to do\" or \"upgrate\" or like. I said in my review what Lemmings & Boulder Dashs goal was. Those might not fit for this game but i could image like you have to build a city with that money or upgrate your Miners with it - a bit like in Terraria or games like...(not in the gameplay)\